    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An Asian species naturalized in eastern North America. It grows to 35-50 feet high. Leaves are five to ten inches long and deep green. Flowers are lavender or purple with yellow stripes and appear at branch tips before leaves sprout in Spring.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
